set default deny

interface mgmt = "ens3"
interface app = "app0"
interface db = "db0"
interface backup = "backup0"

table <app_servers> { 10.40.0.10, 10.40.0.11, 10.40.0.12 }
table <db_hosts> { 10.50.0.10, 10.50.0.11 }
table <dba_hosts> { 10.60.0.10, 10.60.0.11 }
table <backup_hosts> { 10.90.0.10, 10.90.0.11 }
table <blocked> { 10.40.0.66, 10.60.0.66 }

queue db_primary on app bandwidth 40mbit
queue db_backup on backup bandwidth 15mbit

pass in on mgmt proto tcp from any to any port 22 keep state
pass out on mgmt from any to any keep state

block in log (all) from <blocked> to any
pass in log on app proto tcp from <app_servers> to <db_hosts> port 5432 keep state queue db_primary
pass in log (user) on db proto tcp from <dba_hosts> to <db_hosts> port 22 keep state
pass in log (user) on mgmt proto tcp from <dba_hosts> to <db_hosts> port 5432 keep state
pass in on backup proto tcp from <backup_hosts> to <db_hosts> port 5432 keep state queue db_backup
pass out on app proto tcp from <db_hosts> to <app_servers> port 443 keep state queue db_primary

block in log (all) from any to <db_hosts>
block out log (user) from <db_hosts> to any
